"{\"abstract\":\"Document classification is an essential task in many real world applications. Existing approaches adopt both text semantics and document structure to obtain the document representation. However, these models usually require a large collection of annotated training instances, which are not always feasible, especially in low-resource settings. In this paper, we propose a multi-task learning framework to jointly train multiple related document classification tasks. We devise a hierarchical architecture to make use of the shared knowledge from all tasks to enhance the document representation of each task. We further propose an inter-attention approach to improve the task-specific modeling of documents with global information. Experimental results on 15 public datasets demonstrate the benefits of our proposed model.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"144421819\",\"name\":\"B. Tian\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144421819\"},{\"authorId\":\"33603226\",\"name\":\"Yong Zhang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/33603226\"},{\"authorId\":\"114017837\",\"name\":\"J. Wang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/114017837\"},{\"authorId\":\"48950536\",\"name\":\"Chunxiao Xing\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/48950536\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1396342694\",\"name\":\"Kalkidan Fekadu Eteffa\"},{\"authorId\":\"1396342708\",\"name\":\"Samuel Ansong\"},{\"authorId\":\"1962403784\",\"name\":\"Chao Li\"},{\"authorId\":\"46262879\",\"name\":\"Ming Sheng\"},{\"authorId\":\"33603226\",\"name\":\"Yong Zhang\"},{\"authorId\":\"48950536\",\"name\":\"Chunxiao Xing\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1007/978-3-030-60029-7_42\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"6c3da087a3cb0e002d143b29ede10a645fa0010d\",\"title\":\"An Experimental Study of Time Series Based Patient Similarity with Graphs\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/6c3